reviews.review_text: My partner suggested this spot after reading some reviews online, it s a small family friendly joint! The restaurant gets quite busy during lunch, I would suggest plan accordingly and come after the lunch rush. The restaurant holds about 20 people or less, the ambiance is that of a fish spot with seafood art on the walls. Since this was our first stop in Granville Island and wanted to try and see everything, we decided to share the clam chowder and the infamous fish and Chips! Great customer service, daughter was our server, mother washing dishes very humble people. If you are in a hurry, I wouldn t suggest coming here, everything is made fresh to order so it ll take a min. The food was hot and absolutely delicious, one of the best fish and chips around!

I absolutely love a good fish & chips, and Tonys cod fish was delightful, especially when dipped in the creamy tar tar sauce.   Chill atmosphere, great service, and fresh seafood. Cant quite ask for more. After your meal, hop on over to the brewery across the street.

Ducked into this little spot for lunch, best fish & chips (halibut)! The service was excellent and personal, inquiring about our visit to Vancouver. Great lunch experience and well worth the short wait for a table!

The freshest, biggest and absolutely delicious Oysters I have ever had! The front of house staff greet you warmly every time and we were able to be sat immediately. Not long after ordering they bring out their incredible Oysters. We went to Tonys for quick oysters before dinner, after dinner and then another day before lunch! You GOT to come here if you are seeking incredible Oysters.

We wanted to try fish and chips in Vancouver and this place did not disappoint! The salmon was perfect and the chips were extremely delicious too along with the sauces and salad. You can taste the freshness. For someone coming from the coastal part of South Africa we were greatly satisfied with the quality of the food. The customer service was excellent!

This place is a gem! It s a mom n pop shop that serves up classic fried seafood as well as soups and stews at affordable prices without compromising on quantity or quality. I loved the calamari - flavourful, lightly battered and appropriately tender and the oyster stew included three large oysters. It s humble and simple, yet thoughtfully and tastefully decorated, dining space is welcoming and comfortable!

Really glad I came here for lunch. The oysters were so fresh and juicy, good value at $15.99 for half dozen. The fish (cod) and chips were amazing as well. The lunch set with the chowder is great value. Do add another piece (or two) of fish and you will have one super satisfying meal. Recommended!!

This was a great find - we seemed to be the last people to get straight in to a table, as there was a line waiting to get seated the while time we were eating, this little place is so popular! The seafood platter shared between us was fantastic, tasted great and cooked perfectly, not overcooked like some seafood places tend to do. Clam chowder was also really good, definitely homemade. Prices are also very reasonable and the staff friendly, very rushed but always with a smile.

Grabbed the lunch special available during 11:30am - 3pm. Which was breaded cod with tartar sauce also served with fries and cole slaw We also got the breaded oysters. Definitely recommend grabbing this. Service was warm and welcoming.

Just love this cozy little place. We ordered the lunch special which came with clam chowder. Mom and sister had the oysters. Original plans to go to the fish market next door but Im beyond my happy place that we came here instead. This is my happy place and this is my happy meal! Ill be back!!

We came upon this cafe by chance. Walked in soon after it was opened for lunch. We ordered the lunch special for my son and sampler plate for 2 for ourselves. Portions were generous. The lady who ran the place was friendly, efficient and made us feel welcome. Will definitely come again when we visit Granville Isalnd.
No nonsense fish and chips place. Good service, fresh sea food and malt vinegar for your chips. Recommended
The service was great! My son had the lunch special, one piece cod, fries, coleslaw and clam chowder. I had the mussels and they were big. The food was delicious! I would definitely come back.

Ordered the classic fish and chips, it s the best fish and chips i have ever had by far. The crispy skin has no taste of baking soda (or alkaline taste) like how the usual fish and chips would taste like. I d recommend their lunch special for sure because you would get the clam chowder too! It s so creamy <3

Resturant is not big and nothing fancy. Quite busy at lunch hour. Had the lunch special. Soup was great. The batter for the fish was done perfectly. Fries was crispy and not soggy. No stale flavour from oil they deep fry with. Everything was very very good. Suprised at how good this is! 100% Better fish & chips than next door.

I m an English person visiting Vancouver on a study abroad, and let me tell you the batter for the fired cod tastes like the ones in England! Come here, you won t regret it! It s amazing, friendly staff and great prices
Nice little  restaurant.  Great fresh tasting  seafood.  Phenomenal  service.  Will definitely  be back for the fries. Best so far in Vancouver

A small seafood place in Granville Island! Food is pretty tasty! It gets crowded around lunch or dinner time! Fortunately, we came here for an early dinner. When we left, people needed to wait for tables.
Cozy place with great food!

reviews.reviewer_name: Dini and Kasun - The Flavor Bender
reviews.review_text: Ordered fish and chips. It was delicious, fresh and good portions!  Its a small and cozy place! Fast and friendly service too!

First off, the staff was so friendly. It was super busy but the lady managed to get a table for us quickly, the food was delicious and tasted so fresh ! I ordered the salmon burger and it was incredible and filling. Definitely would try again.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback. Glad that you are enjoying your time at our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: Great fish and chips! Super quick service as well for a good price!

Stopped in today as another place closer to me was still not open, so glad I did. I was proptly greeted by a loveley young lady. was shown to a table and placed my order. The fish and chips special was fabulous, 1 peice of cod, chips ,coleslaw and a small bowl of chowder. Very tasty. this will be my granville island go-to place. perfect balance of quality, price and freindly service.
Hands down the best prawn cocktail I have ever had! Super nice staff, cocktail sauce is off the chain!! Prawns...clutch AF.
As a non-local I must say Id consider this a hidden gem on Granville Island. Everything was delicious and the service was fast and friendly! Must visit !
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you so much for your rating and feedback. Glad that you enjoy our foods and the time in our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: Amazing food. Service was friendly and fast. It isnt a fancy spot but the food and service is what matters. Highly recommend
Has one of the best oyster burgers. Nice seafood menu. Beautiful spot to eat on Granville Island
Had the fish & chips and the oysters. Really good and filling!

Loved every part of this restuarant! I ordered fresh oysters, calamari, halibut fish and chips, and seafood special (best). The halibut fish and chips tasted alright still bit dry which isnt what I like but their cod is the best cod i have ever eaten! Not dry, the right type of moist and soft which didnt need much of tarter sauce because it was perfect just the way it was! I went there with my family and we shared every plate together so ordering the seafood special and oysters were the best and is easy to divide up! Best service! The waitresses and waiters were nice. The place seems to get really busy easily so be sure to sprint there to get a good spot (especially if you have a big group) and this is the best place for families to have a get together! Very family friendly place and comfy.

This little shop is a diamond in the rough. In amongst the thicket of tourist traps that is Granville Island, Tonys definitely stands out as being more local-oriented. What it lacks in luxury it makes up for with good ol fashioned hospitality - and plenty of it! The staff even talked with me using my name, which I had written down on the waiting list. That was certainly a welcomed surprise. And the food? Well youll just have to try it for yourself. But with how good youll feel by the time you get it, how could it possibly taste anything less than spectacular?
The food and atmosphere was greatly appreciated. It was fast and so tasty the fish & chips

After a long day of roaming around in Vancouver,  Tonys fish and chips literally brightened my day. We did had a little situation while waiting for food but the manager Terry was amazing enough to quickly jump on it and resolve within no time, being the sweetest and most caring Manager. His words  I just want you to enjoy  Thank you so much Terry. Its a must visit place when in Vancouver.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Mr. Ali, thank you for your rating and feedback. I m glad and happy to hear that you are enjoying our foods. I m also would like to say thank you for giving me a chance to try, resolve and overcome the situation that you having. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: Loved the fresh oysters here. Friendly service as well!!!

The food was delicious and there was quick service. Given the portions of the food, this was well worth the price. I got 2 pieces of Cod, chips, and the clam chowder soup. I ended up having to take some of it home with me!

Have to go early to avoid a queue during peak hours and weekends but the fish n chips are amazing!!! Would recommend the oysters too because they are so fresh! One of the best fish n chips Ive eaten although its a bit pricey but worth it :) the chips are slightly soggy but other than that, its a solid meal

The fish was excellent. Crispy and not too much batter.  It was a bit salty but Im not used to food having salt nowadays. The fries was really great and fresh. Only had a few pieces due to dietary requirement. The server gave me excellent service, she even asked me if I like ice in my water. Not too many servers asked me that lately.
Nice little family restaurant.   Clam chowder was very good plus the fish and chips were tasty!   Would definitely return!
Really good fish & chips. The fish was cooked perfectly and bigger than I expected. The staff was very friendly. Great service!
Loved the place! Very cozy and homely atmosphere, and great service! Food was also delicious! Thank you!!
Of all the places we have eaten fish and chips lately, this one is the best. The fish is a decent size and the batter is crispy and not overdone. Service is also fast and friendly.
Unassuming and small. Well worth it. Value priced compared to some of the other seafood on the island. Id go back.
Located in Grandville Island - Great fish and chips, very tasty and good customer service. Price $$ totally worth it.

EDIT August 17th, 2023 I never thought I would say this but the quality went down big time! the soup was so thick, the spoon could stay up - the batter was thick and the fries were cold - let us hope that it is because it is tourist season and they are too busy to cook properly -
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your feedback and rating. Glad that you enjoying your time at our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: Great little find with simple decor. I had the mussels and they were delicious. The place was full but has a little counter which worked just fine for a solo traveler.

It was listed as a top ten place to eat in Vancouver in our guide book and we were not disappointed. Excellent, fresh seafood and fish in a cafe environment. Excellent service and they have beer on tap from the Granville Island Brewery across the road.

I don t have pictures of the food because we ate it so quickly but their 2 piece halibut and chips and the clam chowder were amazing! Super tiny no frills spot, we were seated and served quickly, and the food was standout. Absolutely coming back!
A unique, warm and cozy place. Had the lunch special. Plenty of food and was delicious.
Yummy   fish   and chips   I love the halibut! Nice and friendly staff
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and kind comments. Glad that you enjoy our foods & services. We looking forward to see you again soon. Stay safe & well :)

reviews.review_text: Amazing fish and chips. I even loved the coleslaw. Raw oysters were great and we had a banana fosters special for dessert. The service was outstanding and they were super nice to our kiddos. Will definitely go again.
Beautiful and tasty experience! The place its pretty warm to enjoy Food
Halibut fish is what you need to order! Fresh, HOT, delicious. We tried their calamari- it came out rubbery. We were not a fan. However their halibut fish was on point!
I tried many fish and chips in Vancouver and Richmond but this is the one I like the most. Fresh seafood, crispy batter, amazing slaw, and best yam fries ever!
Oh my this was an awesome choice for lunch!!! Large pieces of haddock that were not greasy and the batter was so light and crispy. Came with thick cut fries. Service was fast and friendly.

Another wonderful time at Tonys Fish & Oysters on Granville Island. This is my go to place when I visit Vancouver yearly. Food is always on point, the atmosphere quiet and homey, and the staff always experienced and kind. Food : 5/5
Everything is delicious, the attention of the staff is great, definitely I will come back

Decided to try this place because I didnt want to line up for food inside the public market.  I was afraid it would be one of those tourist trap kind of restaurants because of its convenient location right by the entrance to Granville Island. We ordered 2 piece cod with fries to-go (because of Covid restrictions). Ordering and service was fast. Fish was fresh and tender, batter was perfectly fried and not too oily.  Also really loved the fries!  Great value.. two of us shared this plate and were both full.  Will definitely come back and try the rest of the menu.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your feedback and rating. We are looking forward to see you again soon. Stay safe and well :)

reviews.review_text: Excellent fish and chips lunch! The only problem (which wasnt even a problem) was I ordered halibut and received salmon but immediately she came over and told me they will make me the halibut so they actually gave me the salmon for FREE!! The hand cut fries were so good! Very friendly staff (Hamasa was our waitress; this lady is the example of what customer service excellence should be) and very good prices. Small and cozy place. Will be definitely coming back again and telling everyone.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Susan McAusland, Thanks for taking the time to give us your feedback and we do apologize for the misunderstanding that had happened. We are glad to hear that you were happy with your experience with our staff. We can assure you that with your feedback our service will improve even better. Thanks for your time and we hope to see you soon.

reviews.review_text: Good food with reasonable price. Service was great. Id recommend a visit!
Best fish & chips since living in the UK. Small shop, inviting atmosphere, and great service. A perfect lunch stop for a day on Granville Island.
Really nice people, and the food is just as good! Definitely for those who like fish and chips! They even have dessert! Gives off a good hang out vibe.
Delicious seafood gem here Fresh crispy Friendly staff Nice street view
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & comments. Glad that you like our foods & services. Looking forward to see you again soon. Stay safe & well :)

reviews.review_text: Fantastic Fish & Chips! I really appreciate the atmosphere and simplicity of this restaurant
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Mr. Matthew, thank you for your feedback and rating. Glad that you enjoy our foods and your time in the cafe. We are looking forward to see you soon :)

reviews.review_text: Excellent calamari, excellent value, good quality fish and hand cut chips. Staff service excellent

I had been there for lunch special fish and chips for couple months, the service are great and the manager/waitresses lady is always really friendly! The food is fast and served hot. Overall good portion with good price, you cant go any wrong with it.

We waited almost 40 minutes to be seated... Im glad we did. The place is cozy seating 6 at a bar and, Im guessing, at most 24 more - max seating ~30. But do you care? Come a little early or past the peak and youll be fine. The clam chowder was among the best Ive had, fish and chips, and halibut - along with a native Granville brewed ale - it was just perfect. Such friendly staff - the lady who served us went above and beyond, voluntarily splitting a family style order to make it easy for us to enjoy! She has been with Tonys for 12 years over three ownerships - now that means a lot! On Granville Island - youve got to treat yourself to wholesome food and good old Canadian hospitality!

Excellent service! One of the places you could dine causally at a quite affordable price. We ordered fish n chips (Halibut), a pound of clams and breaded oysters. It was definitely tasty for the value. (Mind u this is a premium location. Please do not expect to dine cheap in Granville Island. I read some of the ridiculous comments here complaining its pricey.) It was a busy place but the waitresses were quick and personal without rushing us. And we have a baby and a toddler. We ll definitely go back next time.

This is the second time we ve eaten here and it is a delicious place to visit for lunch. The lunch special includes a cup of clam chowder and fish and chips. We also got some muscles and they were the best we ve ever eaten. The only downside is that it is a very small sitting room with only 3 tables open because of covid so come early! Will definitely be back for more!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & feedback. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: If your in the Granville Island area and looking for great fish and chips, Tonys is an awesome choice. Foods great, service is fast and friendly. The restaurant is a tiny place. At times you can be shoulder to shoulder with other diners, but no one seems to be complaining. The food there is worth it.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, Thank you so much for your rating & feedback. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: Great experience in a touristy area.  Youll pay for the experience but the food is high quality.

If you find yourself looking for a good affordable place to get quality fish and chips around Granville, Tonys is for you. Small but comfortable.  I came during a quieter time, still pretty full, but no wait! I was debating between the cod or the salmon fish and chips.  Waitress said I could have both, great!  Wait time was not long, under 10 minutes.  Good looking, fair sized portions, ( I got the 2 piece ).  Salmon was good, Cod light and flakey, both battered to a light crisp perfection.  Fries were good, well done in house.  Delicious coleslaw, not too creamy which I found perfect.  Tartar is tasty, you can tell its made in house. All in all, good tasty eats that wont blow your mind, but are what you are hoping for from fish and chips.  Service was friendly and helpful.  Price was around $19.00 for the 2 piece fish and chips. Would come back if Im ever in the area again!
What a lovely quaint place. The service is fabulous and the food is delicious. There is a very limited menu, but the food is prepared and served very quickly! Cant wait to go back!
Had the breaded deep fried oysters and yam fries to go...great food..friendly service
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback. We are looking forward to see you again. Stay safe :)

reviews.review_text: Service was quick and friendly. Food was fresh and delicious

I would like to commend the lady who waited on us. Im sorry I did not get your name. We were there Thursday Oct 18th @ 5pm. If I had a restaurant, Id hope my staff was as good as you. The service you provided was amiable. Food was probably on the average side coming from fish and chips in Australia but havent had better in Vancouver.
Really good place for a quick bite. The fosh and chips is really good!!
Ordered Raw Oysters, Fish&Chips (cod) and Mussels. You could taste they were freshly made, nice and quick service. We d come here again!

Living land locked, was looking forward to some excellent seafood while visiting Vancouver and Tonys was the place to go. The fish (of the fish and chips) has a great texture inside and out. The location in Granville is small and busy, but it is well worth the wait.
I had the halibut and my mom had the cod. Both were delicious. Crunchy outer layer and flaky, moist interior.
Have to wait yet definitely worth it. Oyster is good, cod is delicious. Would come again

Cafe is an odd pick for a name, as this is much more like a fish and chip shop with some upscale additions to the menu. They have the local Granville Island Ale/Lager on tap, no doubt from the brewery right across the street-- the ale was well-balanced: not too hoppy, not too malty, and a great complement to the fish and chips. If you get anything here, get the seafood platter, which is a little of everything plus some garlic butter sauce. I dont know if the chef went to the nearby culinary school, but if she did, it certainly shows. The food was fantastic: perfectly seasoned, neither over- nor under-done. It is a bit cramped, having 6 or 7 small tables plus a bar in a space where I would use 4 tables, but the food and excellent service are well worth it.
Delicious and reasonably priced food in Granville Island. Also a nice option to get non-breaded fish and chips, with great portions. Service is prompt and very friendly.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback l. Glad that you enjoy your time at Tony s. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: I definitely enjoyed the platter for two because it gives me more variety of deep fried seafood for me to eat. Squids? Check. Oysters? Check. Halibut? Check. Ideally, your date would enjoy a great greasy spoon load of fish and chips, and its definitely best to visit two hours before closing time if you want peace and quiet atmosphere

I came in for a quick bite before peak dinner hours. I ordered half a dozen raw oysters and they were good. Service was good and quick. The place isnt too big so get here early if you are really interested

A little pricey but great food and location. We came twice during our viit and had some local beers (great), chowder, fish & chips, salmon.and oysters, all good. Staff is really friendly and you get views toward the water. Id recommend.
Sandy was so nice and the fish and chips here is the best! Price is ok and the place is cozy too. Ill be back and bring my wife and kids.
Great  small little seafood place  on Granville island Good prices too. Food
I love their fish and chips! And the portions are huge!!
Friendly sever and the food come out very quickly.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback. Hope you enjoy our foods. Looking forward to see you again. Stay safe :)

reviews.review_text: Great fish and chips (we had the halibut). Friendly staff, especially Sandra. Excellent service. Good prices. If you prefer bigger portions, order the three piece.
This was a beautiful place right by the ocean, with a great view overlooking a gorgeous landscape, the food was a little expensive but wayy worth it.

Amazing! My first meal on my first visit to Vancouver and it was delicious. Had the seafood platter for one and it has a good mix of cod, fried oysters, buttered crab, mussels, clams and scallops. Small space but great atmosphere.

Wow. Amazing. Such a good deal for moist, crunchy, flavourful cod and crunchy chips. The coleslaw with the meal is also amazing. Tony really has a way around the mouth feels. Will be coming back here!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you so much for your rating & feedback. We are happy and glad that you like our foods. Looking forward to see you soon. Stay safe & well :)

reviews.review_text: Very delicious fish and chips! And clam chowder.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & feedback. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: This place must appear in a travel guide, as there are usually tourists noshing here. It is not big, and not a great place for more than four people. There is a signup sheet for diners waiting for a table. They dont take reservations. Being on Granville Island, they have access a variety of very fresh fish.
Pretty great fish burger. The side of onion rings wasnt an afterthought. They were actually delicious. Fresh Granville Island on tap. What more could you ask for?

Teeny tiny place with a wonderful server who is passionate about the food. Delicious fried oysters and fish & chips. I had to sign up to get in for two people on a paper outside. We only waited about 10 to 15 minutes.
Very good and fresh. Quick service
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you so much for your feedback and rating. Glad you enjoy our foods and time in our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: Small restaurant with big flavour. Fresh fish, great choices, friendly staff. The 2pc fish and chips are worth splitting if you also order an appetizer.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & comment. We hope to see you soon. Stay safe :)

reviews.review_text: Awesome fish and chips! Do try the calamari as well. Owners and crew were very friendly and welcoming. Keep up the brilliant work and food!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello, Thank you for your rating and encouraging feedback. We re looking forward to see you again soon :)

reviews.review_text: The food is always great there. The waitress is so nice and very welcomed customers. You will never feel a rushy or push even you can tell that this is a very busy store. Always a great choice.
